{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/automatic-research-recruiting","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Most teams know that talking to users frequently is a key habit to increase empathy, de-risk projects, find innovation opportunities. At Petal, where “listen with curiosity” and “our job is never done” are company values, this is no different.</p>\n<p>In practice, though, scheduling and executing user interviews is messy, time-consuming and can feel like a burden for teams that are used to moving fast. Querying the base, emailing back-and-forth to find the best time, screening, and signing NDA docs with multiple candidates at the same time can easily eat away a good chunk of someone’s calendar.</p>\n<p>When kicking off Petal’s research program, it has been our goal from the start to unblock user interviews by getting rid of the recruiting overhead and make it “just happen”. I partnered with Jack Docal, my marketing colleague and automation wizard, to find a better way.</p>\n<p>Instead of designing a specific research study or topic, for this project our philosophy was “let’s get the users coming, and no matter what we show them, we’ll learn something every week”</p>\n<h2>The workflow</h2>\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 43.11111111111111%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Diagram of the apps we used to automate recruiting\"\n        title=\"Diagram of the apps we used to automate recruiting\"\n        src=\"/static/d258cd3ebd5b5fd76a7ade3ef6c81fbb/d61c2/automated-research-workflow-4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d258cd3ebd5b5fd76a7ade3ef6c81fbb/fc2a6/automated-research-workflow-4.png 450w,\n/static/d258cd3ebd5b5fd76a7ade3ef6c81fbb/1cfc2/automated-research-workflow-4.png 900w,\n/static/d258cd3ebd5b5fd76a7ade3ef6c81fbb/d61c2/automated-research-workflow-4.png 1800w,\n/static/d258cd3ebd5b5fd76a7ade3ef6c81fbb/b2313/automated-research-workflow-4.png 2700w,\n/static/d258cd3ebd5b5fd76a7ade3ef6c81fbb/75ac7/automated-research-workflow-4.png 3600w,\n/static/d258cd3ebd5b5fd76a7ade3ef6c81fbb/78605/automated-research-workflow-4.png 3878w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Diagram of the apps we used to automate recruiting</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n<ol>\n<li>NPS survey</li>\n<li>Opt-in</li>\n<li>Screener questions</li>\n<li>NDA and Agreement signing</li>\n<li>Scheduling a time</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The automated workflow uses a mix of tools: Iterate, Zapier, Segment, Google Sheets, and Calendly.</p>\n<p>Everything starts on our NPS survey, sent to members after they’ve been using the card for a while. On this survey, there’s an opt-in question that asks them if they’d be interested in joining a research session.</p>\n<p>If they say yes, they’re taken to a quick screener designed to filter out technical people folks. If they pass the screener, they receive an email with a link to sign NDA documents, and from there are taken to Calendly, where they can find the time that best suits them.</p>\n<p>A Zoom call is created, and they get a last confirmation email with instructions on how to get prepared for the call.</p>\n<h2>Results</h2>\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1476px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 72%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Schedule full of interviews!\"\n        title=\"Schedule full of interviews!\"\n        src=\"/static/59f25c7fde1650d129796e378b3b1dee/913a1/automated-research-schedule-4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/59f25c7fde1650d129796e378b3b1dee/fc2a6/automated-research-schedule-4.png 450w,\n/static/59f25c7fde1650d129796e378b3b1dee/1cfc2/automated-research-schedule-4.png 900w,\n/static/59f25c7fde1650d129796e378b3b1dee/913a1/automated-research-schedule-4.png 1476w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1476px) 100vw, 1476px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Schedule full of interviews!</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n<p>When we turned the workflow on, we got 10 users scheduled in a week’s time, and that’s with a low sample of NPS surveys sent. Getting this same number with a hands-on recruiting outreach would have taken much longer, and now we have the ability turn it on or off depending on the demand.</p>\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 42%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"And of course, the moment of truth :)\"\n        title=\"And of course, the moment of truth :)\"\n        src=\"/static/1e2e4acb67930bd793148c10daed0678/d61c2/automated-research-user.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1e2e4acb67930bd793148c10daed0678/fc2a6/automated-research-user.png 450w,\n/static/1e2e4acb67930bd793148c10daed0678/1cfc2/automated-research-user.png 900w,\n/static/1e2e4acb67930bd793148c10daed0678/d61c2/automated-research-user.png 1800w,\n/static/1e2e4acb67930bd793148c10daed0678/b2313/automated-research-user.png 2700w,\n/static/1e2e4acb67930bd793148c10daed0678/75ac7/automated-research-user.png 3600w,\n/static/1e2e4acb67930bd793148c10daed0678/61ff6/automated-research-user.png 5904w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">And of course, the moment of truth :)</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n<h2>Next Steps</h2>\n<p>This automated flow, of course, does not cover all the user research bases. It’s biased towards people who have already been using the card; towards people who are comfortable going through our many partners’ tools; and does not help us conduct studies with people in a specific state or journey.</p>\n<p>We’re working on many other initiatives to ensure our teams have the best evidence they can to make user-centered decisions: automated surveys, contextual feedback entry-points in-app, A/B testing frameworks, data democratization, and our internal empathy gauge. Keep tuned to hear more about them all.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"February 13, 2020","path":"/blog/automatic-research-recruiting","title":"Automated User Research Recruiting","topics":["research","Design Ops"],"subtitle":"Talking to users every week","problem":"Recruiting users for research is time-consuming","solution":"An automated, self-service scheduling workflow","impact":"Recurring interview sessions scheduled at the press of a button","color":"#ffefeb","where":null,"learn_more":null,"team":["Jack Docal"],"myrole":"Main advocate, project lead, and interviewer.","link":"http://www.petalcard.com","link_label":"Petalcard.com","cover_image":{"publicURL":"/static/b9336530e4f33b5cc89e5b7b223c1e3a/automated-research-11.png","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/b9336530e4f33b5cc89e5b7b223c1e3a/73c85/automated-research-11.png","srcSet":"/static/b9336530e4f33b5cc89e5b7b223c1e3a/d4144/automated-research-11.png 175w,\n/static/b9336530e4f33b5cc89e5b7b223c1e3a/a5370/automated-research-11.png 350w,\n/static/b9336530e4f33b5cc89e5b7b223c1e3a/73c85/automated-research-11.png 700w,\n/static/b9336530e4f33b5cc89e5b7b223c1e3a/4ff95/automated-research-11.png 1050w,\n/static/b9336530e4f33b5cc89e5b7b223c1e3a/54967/automated-research-11.png 1400w,\n/static/b9336530e4f33b5cc89e5b7b223c1e3a/e3ac0/automated-research-11.png 6400w","sizes":"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"prev":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/petal-before-and-after","title":"Before and after bits","subtitle":"Quick-wins and everyday work.","cover_image":{"publicURL":"/static/bcb598f424c9d3318804405989a1d65c/petal.png"}}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/petal-feedback","title":"Collecting in-app feedback","subtitle":"Measuring user satisfaction in an actionable way","cover_image":{"publicURL":"/static/15dd77281532daa7a4f030880ed90683/petal-feedback-2.png"}}}}}}